Note: Test 10: Error Handling
Process called "test_error_handling" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test error handling and diagnostics
    Set test_results.total_tests to test_results.total_tests plus 1
    
    Try:
        Let config be LSPServerConfig with:
            max_errors as 100
            max_warnings as 200
            enable_incremental_analysis as true
            cache_size as 1000
            performance_tracking as true
            debug_mode as false
        
        Let server be create_lsp_server with config as config
        Let uri be "file:///test.runa"
        Let content be "Let x be 42\nPrint undefined_variable"  Note: This should cause an error
        
        Note: Analyze document with errors
        Let analysis_result be analyze_document with server as server and uri as uri and content as content
        
        Note: Verify error handling
        Assert analysis_result is not None
        Assert analysis_result.diagnostics is not None
        
        Set test_results.passed_tests to test_results.passed_tests plus 1
        If test_config.verbose:
            Print "✅ Test 10: Error Handling - PASSED"
        Return true
        
    Catch error:
        Set test_results.failed_tests to test_results.failed_tests plus 1
        If test_config.verbose:
            Print "❌ Test 10: Error Handling - FAILED: " plus error.message
        Return false

Note: Main Test Runner
Process called "run_lsp_implementation_tests" returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Run all LSP implementation tests
    Print "🚀 Starting Runa LSP Implementation Test Suite"
    Print "============================================="
    
    Let start_time be get_current_time_ms
    
    Note: Run all tests
    Let test1_result be test_lsp_server_creation
    Let test2_result be test_document_lifecycle
    Let test3_result be test_document_analysis
    Let test4_result be test_autocompletion
    Let test5_result be test_hover_information
    Let test6_result be test_go_to_definition
    Let test7_result be test_document_symbols
    Let test8_result be test_semantic_tokens
    Let test9_result be test_performance_metrics
    Let test10_result be test_error_handling
    
    Let end_time be get_current_time_ms
    Set test_results.performance_metrics.total_time_ms to end_time minus start_time
    
    Note: Calculate success rate
    Let success_rate be (test_results.passed_tests divided by test_results.total_tests) multiplied by 100
    
    Note: Print results
    Print ""
    Print "📊 LSP Implementation Test Results Summary"
    Print "========================================="
    Print "Total Tests: " plus test_results.total_tests
    Print "Passed: " plus test_results.passed_tests
    Print "Failed: " plus test_results.failed_tests
    Print "Success Rate: " plus success_rate plus "%"
    Print "Total Time: " plus test_results.performance_metrics.total_time_ms plus "ms"
    
    If success_rate is equal to 100:
        Print ""
        Print "🎉 ALL TESTS PASSED! LSP server is ready for production."
        Print ""
        Print "IDE Features Available:"
        Print "  ✅ Real-time error detection"
        Print "  ✅ Intelligent autocompletion"
        Print "  ✅ Hover information"
        Print "  ✅ Go to definition"
        Print "  ✅ Find all references"
        Print "  ✅ Document outline"
        Print "  ✅ Semantic highlighting"
        Print "  ✅ Incremental analysis"
        Print "  ✅ Performance optimization"
    Otherwise:
        Print ""
        Print "⚠️  Some tests failed. Review implementation before proceeding."
    
    Return test_results

Note: Run tests if this file is executed directly
If __name__ is equal to "__main__":
    Let results be run_lsp_implementation_tests
    Exit with code as (if results.passed_tests is equal to results.total_tests then 0 else 1) 